title: For Sale:  Golden Tiger 7.62x39 1000 round case
postcontent:
I have a 1000 round case of golden tiger 7.62x39 ammo for sale.  I am asking 350 for it since the lower quality wolf/tula are selling for 275 or more when you can find them and THIS is NOT AVAILABLE anymore.  Look for it for sale even online!

In response to the person who posted the tula from CTD it is over 275 shipped to your door for much lower quality ammo.  Golden Tiger is better than the other offerings in many ways. 
1) It has a higher velocity by over 100 FPS
2) It has a boat tail for better accuracy and distance shooting
3) It has sealed primers and projectiles for a round that does not have issues with moisture and storage over time similar to mil spec ammo.
4) The ammo also has a much more consistent powder charge.
5)  One addition feature is a there is an air pocket built into the nose of the bullet which causing tumbling once entering target and will do far more damage which is good for hunting or self defense.

Again if you feel that Tula, Wolf, Bear ect are good enough for you do not spend the extra cash for better quality but do not pretend that these are exact equivalents!

title: For Sale:  Barrett M82A1 CQ 20" NEW 82 50 BMG AWC Turbodyne
postcontent:
AWC Turbodyne: The AWC Turbodyne X is absolutely the most compact, effective, and quiet .50 caliber suppressor available on the market today. Constructed of 100% stainless steel and 360 degree circumferentially welded the Turbodyne produces less noise than a .22LR. The bullet impact can be heard and is the primary source of sound while the lack of concussion allows for hours of comfortable shooting.

The Turbodyne X can be fitted to most semi-auto and bolt action .50 BMG rifles, mounting directly to the current muzzle break threads without modification to the gun.

Here are a few things about this rifle from the manufacturer:

"Unlike other semi-automatic .50 BMG rifles, the Model 82A1 is completely reliable. Its chamber is chrome-plated and dimensioned for both civilian and military ammunition. The extractor and ejector are proven to work under any condition, and close tolerances on every part allow it to function in all environments.

Its re-engineered muzzle brake, dual barrel springs and long mainspring design make the 82A1 comfortable and, dare we say, exciting to shoot.

The Model 82A1 fits into a regular sized carrying case. Although it is transported as a disassembled upper and lower receiver, it can be ready to fire in under a minute by simply inserting two assembly pins through both receivers. The scope remains mounted on the upper receiver, maintaining scope zero. The rifles M1913 optics rail is tapered 27 MOA to take full advantage of the scopes elevation travel."

This rifle actually will fit in the case fully assembled, which is a nice advantage. No need to mess with assembly while out in the field. Also, the chrome-lined barrel will make it easier to clean.

title: For Sale:  Norinco Mak 90 (AK47) in 5.56
postcontent:
Norinco Mak 90 (AK-47) chambered in 5.56x45. This is a low serial number gun that was most likely caught in customs when the 1990 ban was enacted and restamped from an 84s to a Mak 90 to meet import requirements. Serial # is 9005xx where the 90 part was added to indicate the import year. This Mak 90 DOES NOT appear to have been defanged. It has the 'fangs' on the bottom of the front sight block and the original threaded barrel with original flash hider. Virtually all Mak90's have had their barrels turned down or welded to remove the threads and had the fangs/bayonet lug ground off. As you can see this has original threads and the fangs/cleaning rod still intact. A very few Mak 90's early in the import ban process got through customs without being defanged. This appears to be one. 

For those not familiar with the Mak 90 they are Chinese AK's manufactured in a regular Chinese military arsenal for export. They are not like the crap AK's you can buy in stores today. They have chromed bolts and chromed barrels and are much heavier built and more durable than the versions imported today from non-military arsenal manufacturers.

This Mak 90 has one original Chinese steel magazine which feeds perfectly. It has a square cut, stamped 1.5mm receiver, and all numbers match. Side-folding poly stock, 4 way picatinny rail foregrip, Hogue ergo pistol grip, and 'grippod' front grip with spring loaded bipod. Also has the side mount to install an optics rail and includes the adjustable optics rail. Includes an additional solid poly (non-folding) stock with the cleaning kit inside it that can be put in place of the folding stock. Face to face in Oregon only with Oregon ID. Will not ship.

But i doubt  you will need one because this rifle will flat drive tacks. The custom made laminated stock is designed for hair splitting accuracy from the bench off a bi-pod or off hand shooting. Hunting coyotes punching paper or take it to a prairie dog town. short range or long range this rifle will do it all and impress ya while its doing it. Its a very comfortable stock while shooting. solid cheek weld every time. No searching for cheek placement its there every time you go to shoot. I have shot prone,off the bench,and off of pole cat bi-pod with no problems just to make sure everything felt good if a shot ever presented its self from any position.  This rifle has very low round count i bought it new about 9 months ago. has maybe 35-40 rounds threw it. Has a few safe dings in the stock but nothing i would call major. bore is excellent. Rifle will shoot sub MOA at 200 yards. i have shot 1/2-3/4 inch group at 200 yards with 55gr silver ballistic tip ammo. with a good load development worked up on the rifle im sure it will shoot even better. I bought the rifle for mainly coyote hunting but only went a couple times do to work.  Plus i got a few irons in the fire i got to fund so my loss is your gain. You will not be disappointed in this rifle one bit. Im not and im very picky on how a rifle preforms. Heres what im asking rifle with scope rings for the X-bolt 850.00 OBO the scope on top is a zeiss HD5 lockable target turrets with the varmint ret. Excellent glass very clear spot on adjustments. has the zero stop feature. its a 5-25x50 just a high quality. Built like a tank way better scope the the zeiss conquest. Not even in the same league as the conquest. I would do 1700.00 OBO for the rifle with scope ready to shoot. Or would sale the scope separate for 900.00 OBO i bought the scope new and its got a life time warranty as well.  I belive i still got the factory boxes for both rifle and scope. I need to sale as quick as i can so if ya have any questions please ask and i will get them answered thanks. give me a call or text for any info REDACTED im located in Eldorado


Heres some information i found  on the rifle. just in case i forgot something.

The X-Bolt Varmint Special pushes the concept of function driven design with extreme style. The specially designed wood Laminate stock is crafted by Altamont Paladin, a renowned designer and manufacturer of firearms stocks and grips. This stock, designed to be fired from the prone or bench, is crafted to provide a comfortable firing position for the shooter, reducing fatigue and increasing stability. The "hook" on the bottom of the butt allows for an isometric grip with the non-firing hand and can be used in conjunction with a "rabbit ear" style sandbag.
The ergonomic features of the grip angle, thumb hole stock and cheek rest, are purposed to promote a proper grip that won't shift when firing, and allow excellent alignment with your optic. The vented free float fore arm promotes uniform barrel cooling for minimal Point of Impact shift as more rounds are fired in quick succession.The Paladin stock is designed for advanced varmint shooting. Special attention has been placed on eliminating any weakness that could possibly compromise flexural strength - the end result being a stock that is a superbly accurate platform for shooting from the bench or prone supported positions as well as from the off-hand. Each stock is hand finished, fitted and bedded to each action individually. The resin impregnated wood Laminate is sealed to make it impervious to moisture and temperature affects that can cause warping effects that change Point of Impact and barrel harmonics.The vented free float fore arm promotes uniform barrel cooling for minimal Point of Impact shift as more rounds are fired in quick succession.
• Custom grade Altamont Palidan wood Laminate stock designed for accuracy from the bench, off a bipod and off hand.
• Butt stock hook for isometric grip or use with a sandbag helps to provide steady aim.
• Pistol grip features sharp checkering to reduce movement of the firing hand while squeezing the trigger - the right hand palm swell and ergonomically angled grip promote proper trigger squeeze and a comfortable firing position.
• Thumbhole Stock with raised cheek piece maximizes the surface available for a firm cheek to stock "weld" in different positions - standing, kneeling, sitting and prone.
• Forearm vents are designed to add style while uniformly cooling the barrel - vital to accurate sustained fire.
• Angled fore end palm rest is designed to position your non-firing hand in a comfortable position during off hand shooting
• Heavy barrel causes the rifle to lay in the rest or on a bi-pod with much more stability, also controls barrel whip, vibration, recoil and barrel heating/cooling, further enhancing accuracy.
• Durable low-luster blued finish reduces reflective glare
• Button-rifled barrel is triple checked for quality and individually hand chambered and air gauged to ensure consistency and accuracy.
• The target Crown enables the uniform release of gas as the bullet exits the barrel, preventing a shift in trajectory. The Crown is recessed to protect it from accidental damage that degrades accuracy.
• Free floated barrel eliminates contact interference from the fore-end, enabling the superior barrel craftsmanship to perform consistently and accurately.
• Drilled and tapped for X-Lock scope mounts that use four screws for each base to provide a rock solid optic platform.
• Adjustable Feather Trigger minimizes the "human factor" by eliminating creep and take-up — providing a crisp trigger pull that "breaks like glass."
• Low profile action allows you to mount the scope extremely close to the center of the bore to minimize the offset between point of aim and Point of Impact.
• 60° bolt lift keeps the thumb and fingers clear of the scope when cycling the action and allows the bolt to be operated in a smoother/quicker motion.
• Top-tang safety offers easy accessibility without removing your firing hand from the stock. The shooter can quickly manipulate the safety, or verify the position of the safety, without losing your sight picture or cheek weld.
•Detachable rotary magazine is built from tough polymer and is designed to stop forward movement of the cartridge by contacting the shoulder of the case rather than the tip of the projectile. This prevents bullet tip deformation and recoil induced bullet seating depth change.
•Bolt Unlock Button allows the bolt to be cycled with the safety engaged.
• Innovative Inflex Technology recoil pad uses directional deflection to pull the stock down and away from the face to reduce perceived recoil.
